  "description": [
    "Cory right 1914 y Herbert Kaufman How Old Are You Dont start counting your birthdays they dont r ally count Weve been confusing age with efficiency for far too long Time doesnt shorten an ass ears How far have you developed How sharp are your faculties Quite a few misguided persons still cling to the obsolete notion that there is actually a definite relation between wisdom and whiskers People used to pay far more attention to gray hairs than to gray matter they seemed possessed with the idea that dullards and wine both improved with ripening But neither a blockhead nor a pojr vintage can be transmuted into excellence by the alchemy of age Men mature by processes of thought not by physical devel opment The hour glass is not a safe measure for intellect Everybody with a grownup body isnt possessed of a grownup brain There are millions of grandfathers who cant think as clearly and dont know as much as children We are just beginning to adjust ourselves to the realization that past systems of pedagogy were founded upon the erron eous hypothesis that set standards of training would standardize ability Now we admit that the prime function"
